    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="15"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                <head>15. Telegram 249 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d15fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–255. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-02"
                            >August 2, 1955, 8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d15-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d15-1"/>
                <p>249. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>This morning CHICOM Ambassador Berlin told same source mentioned Mytel 226 that
                    American civilians under arrest in China <pb facs="0065" n="18" type="typeset"
                        xml:id="pg_18"/> now being collected near Peiping in anticipation early
                    repatriation; that CHICOMS are going propose bilateral agreement with US to
                    renounce use force settlement any “international” questions; CHICOMS willing
                    agree not use force against Formosa if can obtain possession Matsu and Quemoy
                    and US recognizes CHICOM “peaceful claim” to Formosa; CHICOMS will not agree any
                    internationalization Fomosa; and <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> is
                    going press me for early FonMin conference preferably September at which all
                    outstanding issues would be discussed. Also last week CHICOMS delivered strong
                    note to Soviets expressing “disapproval” of failure Soviets press Far Eastern
                    matters harder at conference.</p>
                <p>CHICOMS very “irked” with Soviets at this.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
